Date: Thu, 11 Aug 2011 15:30:40 +0100
Subject: mm: swap: Implement generic handlers for swap-related address ops
References: Swap over NFS (fate#304949)
Patch-mainline: no

With the introduction of swap_activate, swap_writepage and
swap_readpage, there is a number of SWP_FILE checks that call a_ops and
fallback to generic handlers. This patch clarifies things by creating
generic versions of these functions that take the same parameters.
This removes the need for SWP_FILE and cleans up the flow slightly.
There are no functional changes.

